companyProfile.companyDescription: Bharat Petroleum Corporation Limited is an India-based company, which is engaged in the business of refining of crude oil and marketing of petroleum products. The Company's businesses include fuels and services, Bharatgas, MAK lubricants, aviation services, gas, industrial and commercial, international trade, proficiency testing, and pipelines. It has a variety of product offerings like petrol, diesel, automotive liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) and compressed natural gas (CNG) along with premium petrol products like Speed and Speed 97. It offers specialized fuel station formats like Ghar, Highway Star, Pure for Sure, and other such services. MAK Lubricants provides lubricants and greases in India and international markets. It has refineries in Mumbai, Kochi and Bina, LPG bottling plants and lube blending plants at various locations. The Company's marketing infrastructure includes a network of installations, depots, retail outlets, aviation fueling stations and LPG distributors.

recentNews.headline: BPCL Dividend: State-run OMC declares final dividend of  ?5 per share for FY25; Record date to be fixed on THIS day
recentNews.intro: BPCL Dividend: BPCL will announce the record date for its final dividend in a separate exchange filing. According to the OMC's statement, the final dividend will be paid within 30 days from the declaration at the annual general meeting.
recentNews.imagecaption: BPCL Dividend: The dividend will be paid 30 days after the declaration of India's second-largest state-run OMC's annual general meeting (AGM). The record date for the dividend will be announced separately. (Image: Pixabay)

recentNews.headline: BPCL Q4 Results: Profit slides 8% YoY to  ?4,392 crore; revenue dips 4%
recentNews.intro: BPCL Q4 Results: Oil market company (OMC) Bharat Petroleum Corporation Limited (BPCL) posted an 8% decline in its consolidated net profit to  ?4,392 crore for the March 2025 quarter, compared with  ?4,789.57 crore in the same quarter last year.
recentNews.imagecaption: BPCL Q4 Results: Profit slides 8% YoY to  ?4,392 crore; revenue dips 4%

recentNews.headline: BPCL, HPCL, Indian Oil shares get bearish calls from analysts despite falling crude oil prices. Here's why
recentNews.intro: Analysts remain bearish on Indian OMC stocks despite falling global crude prices. They anticipate unsustainable auto fuel marketing margins due to potential government excise duty hikes and risks from LPG under-recoveries. JM Financial has a 'Sell' rating on HPCL, IOCL, and a 'Hold' on BPCL.
recentNews.imagecaption: BPCL, HPCL, Indian Oil shares get bearish calls from analysts despite falling crude oil prices. Here's why

recentNews.headline: Coal India, ONGC, BPCL among 5 PSU stocks with highest dividend yields

recentNews.imagecaption: Dividend Stocks; Coal India , Top 5 PSU dividend yield stocks during FY25

recentNews.headline: OMC Stocks: Should you buy HPCL, BPCL, IOC shares amid falling crude oil prices, excise duty hike?
recentNews.intro: The three state-run OMCs, Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Ltd, Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd and Indian Oil Corporation Ltd, saw a sharp movement in their share prices after the government announced a hike in excise duty on petrol and diesel.
recentNews.imagecaption: OMC stocks are down 7%?16% YTD, and the correction has left valuations of OMCs very attractive, analysts said.
